places.address: QXPF+P45 Jama Masjid, Makha Leikai, Imphal, Manipur 795008

featured_reviews.review_id:
Situated on the banks of the Nambul River in Imphal, the Jama Masjid is well constructed which invites the attention of people coming from different part of the world with the grandeur of its construction and magnificent domes. The magnificent mosque has the capacity to house a large gathering for daily prayer. Visiting Jama Masjid during festivals like Eid-Ul-Fitr and Eid-Ul-Zuha would help you get an an experience and get filled up sense of holiness.

HOW TO REACH?
There are rickshaws available at the main Ponda Bus stand which can take you to the site of the Safa Masjid.

BEST TIME TO VISIT
A visit to Jama Masjid can be made at any time of the year, but consider visiting during the winter season i.e., between November and February as the weather remains cool and pleasant. Also, visiting during the festivals would be an ideal choice.

ENTRY FEES
There is no entry fees to Jama Masjid.
